<br>
All of these have been made to further the enjoyment and gaming efforts of the members. It is a management tool for our guild.<br>
<br>
The Book of Retribution is the work of the Council of Retribution, and can be changed, edited, deleted, or whatever at the decision of that council.<br>
<br>
I hope you will all help make this what it was meant to be : a tool to increase the fun of playing, decrease the hassle of having to debate rules in game and to create an atmosphere appropriate for our world of Sullon Zek !<br>
<br>
Besides the rules put in the book, we have a couple EzBoard rules which all members are required to live by, whether they wish to gain ranks or not. They are :<br>
1 . All members of the BoR guild are required to visit and use (as in post where you want to make a comment) at least a couple times a week, provided you are on the internet that week.<br>
2. All officers of the BoR are required to visit and use this board alot, make comments where necessary and be a visible user of this place. Daily visits will be expected, again provided you are on the internet that day.<br>
3. As the very first thing new members are required to do, is the Roster Profile. They are required to make a roster entry into the forum for the proper house, copy the Template from the Combined Members List forum and fill it out with their own details. At the very least, the top section should be filled out at first.<br>
4. All members, no matter what their rank is, are required to update and keep updated their member roster entry. Most of the sections in there are meant for members to edit, while a few are meant for officers. You will learn which when you join the guild.<br>
5. Failure to adhere to these Message Board requirements can lead to removal from the guild. It is a vital management tool for the guild and we will not accept members who refuse to use it as such.<br>
